  "title": "Freelance Female swim coach",
  "description": "<p><strong>🧠 What You’ll Do:</strong></p><ul><li>Coach and inspire individuals of all ages to reach their swimming goals.</li><li>Conduct one-to-one or group lessons (max 3).</li><li>lesson planning and conducting</li><li>Be an approachable, positive role model with a fun, engaging approach and a talent for coaching that meets individual’s needs.</li></ul><p><strong>✅ Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Min commitment 1 Year</strong></li><li><strong>Female</strong></li><li>Able to swim min 2 strokes</li><li>Coaches are require to travel to client location in either West/East/North East/North/Central/South</li><li>Available on weekdays and/or weekends</li><li>passionate, responsible and patient</li><li>candidates are require to work with children and adults and are responsible for their water safety</li></ul><p><strong>What You Get:</strong></p><ul><li>Earn from MIN $35 per lesson (30 or 45 mins)</li><li>Free In-house coach training or get sponsorship for a coaching license!</li><li>Students assigned near your area based on your availability.</li><li>You are able to choose your assignments based on your schedule, but must be able to commit to the assignment long term.</li></ul>",
